abstract: U.S. stocks rose after FedEx beat earnings expectations and initial claims for unemployment benefits fell. European stocks also gained, but global economic worries led to losses in Asia.
snippet: U.S. stocks rose after FedEx beat earnings expectations and initial claims for unemployment benefits fell. European stocks also gained, but global economic worries led to losses in Asia.
lead_paragraph: Stock indexes snapped a three-day decline as data on jobless claims and manufacturing signaling a strengthening economy overshadowed concern over the European debt crisis.

headline.main: Indexes End 3-Day Swoon On Upbeat Economic Data
headline.print_headline: Indexes End 3-Day Swoon On Upbeat Economic Data
